ConsoleTrace.summary:
The console.trace() method outputs a stack trace to the
Web console.

blockquote.para: Note: In some browsers, console.trace() may also output the sequence of calls and asynchronous events leading to the current console.trace() which are not on the call stack â€” to help identify the origin of the current event evaluation loop.

remarks.para:
See Stack traces in the
documentation for details and examples.
